        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A clinical entity that represents a severe phenotype of Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease characterized by onset occurring in infancy severe motor weakness delayed motor development extremely slow nerve conduction (< 10-12 m/s) areflexia and foot deformity. Mutations in the genes <i>PMP22</i> (17p12) <i>MPZ</i> (1q22) <i>EGR2</i> (10q21.1) and <i>PRX</i> (19q13.2) have been implicated."
        },
